OL,3,CBoy hails new-found 'freedom' after
OL,4,C#1.6m treatment
OL,6,FA boy who was one of the first
OL,7,Fchildren to be given a #1.65 million
OL,8,Ftreatment has returned to hospital to
OL,9,Fthank his nurse for his new-found
OL,10,Ffreedom.
OL,12,FAdam Rehman, from Oldham, was given a
OL,13,Fone-time gene editing therapy at Royal
OL,14,FManchester Children's Hospital to cure
OL,15,Fthe blood disorder thalassaemia.
OL,17,FCasgevy, also known as exa-cel, was
OL,18,Fthe first treatment to be licensed
OL,19,Fusing gene-editing tool Crispr, which
OL,20,Fearned its inventors the Nobel Prize
OL,21,Ffor chemistry in 2020.
